Slot Description: the source of description or other element
text of an alternate description

Description: Level of confidence in a statement
Class of evidence that supports an association

Slot Description: An example of a model element
A description of an example value or an abstract description of use

Description: a piece of information that typically describes some piece of biology or is used as support.

Slot Description: A unique identifier for a thing.  Must be either a CURIE shorthand for a URI or a complete URI
The external ontology element that this is a subclass of
Name of the high level ontology class in which this entity is categorized. Corresponds to the label for the biolink entity type class. In a neo4j database this MAY correspond to the neo4j label tag
List of definitions to be mixed in. Targets may be any definition of the same type

Used to extend class or slot definitions. For example, if we have a core schema where a gene has two slots for identifier and symbol, and we have a specialized schema for my_organism where we wish to add a slot systematic_name, we can avoid subclassing by defining a class gene_my_organism, adding the slot to this class, and then adding an apply_to pointing to the gene class. The new slot will be 'injected into' the gene class.

specifies single-inheritance between classes or slots. While multiple inheritance is not allowed, mixins can be provided effectively providing the same thing. The semantics are the same when translated to formalisms that allow MI (e.g. RDFS/OWL). When translating to a SI framework (e.g. java classes, python classes) then is_a is used. When translating a framework without polymorphism (e.g. json-schema, solr document schema) then is_a and mixins are recursively unfolded

Description: the subject or object of a biolink association
person, group, organization or project that provides a piece of information

Any published piece of information. Can refer to a whole publication, or to a part of it (e.g. a figure, figure legend, or section highlighted by NLP). The scope is intended to be general and include information published on the web as well as journals.
information that modifies or qualifies the meaning of a biolink association
the predicate or relationship of a biolink association

Slot Description: A high-level grouping for the relationship_type. AKA minimal predicate. This is analogous to category for nodes.
inverse relationship

Description: the name and description of a subset
Top level class for both associations and named_things

Slot Description: A human-readable name for a thing
a human-readable description of a thing
alternative descriptions and names for an element, which may be attributed to a source
notes and comments about an element intended for external consumption
editorial notes about an element intended for internal consumption
example usages of an element

used to indicate membership of a term in a defined subset of biolink terms used for a particular domain or application (e.g. the translator_minimal subset holding the minimal set of predicates used in a translator knowledge graph)
a reference
a list of Curie prefixes that are used in the representation of instances of the model.  All prefixes in this list are added to the prefix sections of the target models.
a long-form human readable name for a thing
this slot or class can only be used as a mixin -- equivalent to abstract
an abstract class is a high level class or slot that is typically used to group common slots together and cannot be directly instantiated.

a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have comparable meaning. These may include terms that are precisely equivalent, broader or narrower in meaning, or otherwise semantically related but not equivalent from a strict ontological perspective.
a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have strictly equivalent meanings.
a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have a broader, more general meaning. Broader terms are typically shown as parents in a hierarchy or tree.
a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have a narrower, more specific meaning. Narrower terms are typically shown as children in a hierarchy or tree.

a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have a semantically similar but not strictly equivalent, broader, or narrower meaning. Such terms often describe the same general concept from different ontological perspectives (e.g. drug as a type of chemical entity versus drug as a type of role borne by a chemical entity).
a point in time
An IRI for the node. This is determined by the id using expansion rules.
the imports entry that this element was derived from.  Empty means primary source
date on which thing was created. This can be applied to nodes or edges
date on which thing was updated. This can be applied to nodes or edges
map from local identifier to slot
